lenders.name: Julia
lenders.loan_because: I need money to open an account (because my husband worked as a broker, but has not received a salary, because it has no customers) and I plan to live off the commission for the account to meet all the needs of my debt and the cost of my life
lenders.occupational_info:
I am working as a sales marketing in a private company in my country, but the salary that I get out to pay a debt to my boss as well as mortgage payments. So now my husband who worked as a broker (not yet received a penny salary) at a brokerage firm needs funds to open an account so he could get a fixed salary at the company. My husband had to pursue this field for 2 years, but until now have not received a single customer, because he was slow of speech and we do not have the money to open an account in order to show to our prospective customers, but the results are always generated trading profits. Now the fund $ 20,000 that we'll use to open the account, because of the commission that we can, will help meet our needs and solve our debt is in the bank.
Why would we want to borrow funds of $ 20,000 and not $ 10,000? That is because based on an analysis of trading experience and my husband, substantial funds by trading fixed scale of 1 lot, it will minimize the risk of funds being floated to the end.
So, we hope there is a chance for us to get a loan fund, and we are ready to be given the desired schedule of installments along with the payment period.
To all the lenders I say many thanks. Hopefully from this website, many people helped better, thanks to all of you.
